</paragraph>
<paragraph pageNumber="552">types Mus. Comp. Zool. Harvard.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection type="etymology">
<paragraph pageNumber="552">
Etymology L 
<taxonomicName LSID-HNS="urn:lsid:biosci.ohio-state.edu:osuc_concepts:181967" class="Insecta" family="Formicidae" genus="Pheidole" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Pheidole globularia Wilson" lsidName-HNS="Pheidole globularia Wilson" order="Hymenoptera" pageNumber="552" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="globularia">globularia</taxonomicName>
, of a small ball, referring to the head shape of the major.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection type="diagnosis">
<paragraph pageNumber="552">
Diagnosis A member of the 
<taxonomicName LSID-HNS="urn:lsid:biosci.ohio-state.edu:osuc_concepts:33923" class="Insecta" family="Formicidae" genus="Pheidole" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Pheidole perpusilla Emery" lsidName-HNS="Pheidole perpusilla Emery" order="Hymenoptera" pageNumber="552" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="perpusilla">perpusilla</taxonomicName>
group (very small, with 10-segmented antennae), distinguished within the group as follows. Major: head in full-face view 1.IX times broader than long; carinulae originating on the frontal lobes spread laterad away from the midline as they approach the occiput; sides of head posterior to eye lack carinulae, covered only with foveolae; small, triangular process present on postpetiole venter; propodeal spines robust, as long as the basal propodeal face anterior to them; mesosoma, waist, and gaster almost completely devoid of sculpturing.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection type="description">
<paragraph pageNumber="552">Minor: propodeal spines more than half as long as the propodeal face anterior to them; body completely devoid of sculpturing, and entirely smooth and shiny.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageNumber="552">measurements (mm) Holotype major: HW 0.68, HL 0.60, SL 0.36, EL 0.12, PW 0.32. Paratype minor: HW 0.32, HL 0.38, SL 0.32, EL 0.06, PW 0.24. Color Major and minor: concolorous dark yellow.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection type="distribution">
<paragraph pageNumber="552">Range Known only from the type locality.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection type="biology_ecology">
<paragraph pageNumber="552">Biology Unknown.</paragraph>
